{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5c9ef089-c383-4f37-9b69-de0c3083d65e","content":"The project directory doesn't exist yet in this workspace, but I can tell you exactly what to configure. Add these properties to your `.csproj` file:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Required for dotnet tool -->\n  <PackAsTool>true</PackAsTool>\n  <ToolCommandName>my-mcp-server</ToolCommandName>\n\n  <!-- NuGet package metadata -->\n  <PackageId>MyMcpServer</PackageId>\n  <Version>1.0.0</Version>\n  <Authors>YourName</Authors>\n  <Description>An MCP server for …</Description>\n  <PackageProjectUrl>https://github.com/you/MyMcpServer</PackageProjectUrl>\n  <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>\n  <PackageReadmeFile>README.md</PackageReadmeFile>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nKey points:\n\n- **`PackAsTool`** — marks the project as a .NET tool (must be a console app).\n- **`ToolCommandName`** — the CLI command users will run.\n- **`OutputType`** must be `Exe` (default for console apps).\n\n**Build, pack, and publish:**\n\n```bash\ndotnet pack -c Release\ndotnet nuget push bin/Release/MyMcpServer.1.0.0.nupkg \\\n  --api-key YOUR_API_KEY --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n**Users install with:**\n\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g MyMcpServer\nmy-mcp-server          # runs via stdio\n```\n\nWant me to apply these changes to your `.csproj` directly?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6847942c-4255-467b-b5f7-a612e450a4ae","outputTokens":420,"requestId":"F04C:1986A2:1208E4D:1468F14:69F94175"},"id":"aec7fb7e-29fa-4cec-af7c-84a03ee37858","timestamp":"2026-05-05T01:01:49.506Z","parentId":"54f9b0ce-23e3-433d-9bdf-39915d8e97f6"}
